OL,6,FMost were returned to custody for non-
OL,7,Fsexual crimes of violence, accounting
OL,8,Ffor 20 cases, while 17 returned for
OL,9,Fcrimes of dishonesty, and eight for
OL,10,Fboth crimes against society and anti-
OL,11,Fsocial offences.
OL,13,FOther offences ` including damage and
OL,14,Freckless behaviour ` also resulted in
OL,15,Freturns to custody, the report shows,
OL,16,Fbut the specifics were not released.
